  "texts": [
    "The implementation is written in TypeScript and is based on Langium [63], an open-source language engineering tool which supports the Language Server Protocol.",
    "Thanks to Langium, the editor offers built-in syntax-highlighting, syntax checking and autocomplete suggestions.",
    "These suggestions are a useful way to help a user create a prompt, e.g., by suggesting a list of candidate predefined traits.In addition to a graphical user interface (GUI), Impromptu also offers a simple command-line interface (CLI) that makes it possible to generate tool-specific prompts within automated workflows.Furthermore, the Impromptu editor provides users with code generation capabilities.",
    "Given a prompt (or list of prompts), the editor features the generation of Python code to be used to invoke the APIs of online available large language models including that prompt as message.",
    "The code generated also includes methods for testing the model response to the prompt."
